LINE.Text: United Nations Convention on the Rights
The Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (CRPD) and its Optional Protocol (OP)
were adopted on 13 December 2006, as the first comprehensive human rights treaty of the 21
century. It entered into force on 3 May 2008. 2016 marks the 10-year anniversary of the CRPD.

The Conference of State Parties (COSP) to the CRPD
The COSP is the largest and most diverse international disability
meeting in the world. It provides a launching pad to advance the
human rights and inclusion of persons with disabilities in society and
development. The annual Conference sees participation from
